net.alantea.proper

Annotation Type Bind


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
 @Inherited
public @interface Bind
    The annotation Bind, usable only on fields with a type deriving from Property. It is use to bind the annotated field to the property with the given name in the container. The property must have been defined before. The property field content class type must be assignable from the container property content type.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String value
      Property name in the container.

    • Optional Element Summary

        Bidirectional flag. If true, the binding should be bidirectional. If false, the binding should be done to bind the field property to the container property. The default value is 'false'.
